OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBP guilty after worker died
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fin offshore fall           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Energy firm BP has been found guilty of
OL,6, breaching health and safety laws after 
OL,7, a worker died when he fell from an     
OL,8, offshore platform into the sea.        
OL,10,FSean Anderson, 43, fell through an open
OL,11,Fgrating on the Unity installation,     
OL,12,Fabout 112 miles (180km) north-east of  
OL,13,FAberdeen, on 4 September 2014.         
OL,15,FMr Anderson, from the Tyne and Wear    
OL,16,Farea, fell about 72ft (22m) into the   
OL,17,Fwater.                                 
OL,19,FThe jury's verdict followed an         
OL,20,Feight-day trial at Aberdeen Sheriff    
OL,21,FCourt.                                 
